<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I'm not exactly sure what are your specific complaints about the magician class, since your post is a bit hard to read, but it seems that you're unhappy due to the fact that all other classes have pets. That's simply not true.<P>Yodelroy has provided us with a list of classes that have pets. His list is grossely exagerated:<P>Bard - Bards get two Charm songs, with a duration of 18 seconds, which is next to useless.<br><BR>Beastlord - Not much information about this class, but it seems to have one pet spell, with several pet-only buffs. We'll have to see where that goes.<br><BR>Cleric - They have no pet or charm spell. I just reviewed the CR list. Where did you get that?<br><BR>Druid - Druids have charm spells that only work on animals, and a ONE pet spell at level 55, which is another animal. I doubt that it has the combat ability of a magician's pets, and I'm quite sure it doesn't have any special abilities like spells.<br><BR>Necro - The Necromancer does have very good pets, but all necromancers agree that the mages' pets are better.<br><BR>Enchanter - Enchanters do have pets, but they very weak compared to a mage's pet, and they're uncontrollable. They have excellent charming abilities, but you still have a duration limit and the post-charm aggro problem to deal with.<br><BR>Shadowknight - A weaker version that the necromancer. Since it's already been said that the necromancer's pet is weaker than a mage's, it goes without saying that the Shadowknight's pet is no contest.<br><BR>Shaman - The shaman has some of the druid's lower-level charm spells, and it only gets them at level 34. At this level, shamans also get their first real pet spells. The biggest one they get is Spirit of the Howler at level 55, which summons a level 34-37 pet with 1400-1800 HP and which does 48-53 damage. That's a far cry from the monster pets cast by magicians at higher levels. The pets you get with the level 51 mage's pet are reported to have roughly 2700 HP, which is TWICE the HPs of the shaman's howler.<br><BR>Wizard - Wizards get no pet. They *may* be getting familliars with SoL, but nobody really knows what the familiars will do. Chances are they'll be similar to enchanter pets.<P>Mages might not have exclusive rights on pet in EQ, but they can claim to have the most powerful pets. A mage who uses his pets well can easily solo his way to the higher levels, and they would make a great addition to any group.<P>Linanie
</FONT>
