I have to agree here. We may have the best pets. But no class relies so much on their pets AND is so defenseless as a mage. A root spell (earth based) or stun spell (air based) would imo help the mage class much more than for example the Malise line (dont get me wrong...i love the Malise spells). Hard to understand why mages get no defensive capabilities at all. Ok our pets usually can keep us from getting hit. But get one add, and dont manage to get yer pet off from the first target so it fights both mobs...you know the result. Why does virtually EVERY casting class get a root or at least snare spell, just not mages?<P>Oh btw. I think our class is very balanced as it is (at least to mid 50's, cant tell more as i'm not further yet). But WHY would even the most simple defense spell make the mage class unbalanced? Root, stun, shield skin...there are enough possibilites!
