<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
What has been mentioned before are all good points, though many are subjective or mere opinions. <P>My opinion is that the presence or absence of pet is less important than the tactics involved with each pet class. Every one of the classes with true pets (Necro, SK, Shaman and enchanter) have some form of damage management/prevention. This can take the form of Fear, SoW, Snare, etc... In the case of an enchanter, most enchanters over level 20 just don't bother, and concentrate on crowd control and other things where a pet would interfere. For a SK and NEcro, pet is really just a glorified DoT while fearkiting. Same applies to Shaman pet. YES the pets are weaker, but that is mmaterial because pet doesn't ever get hit.<P>My thought on improving the balance is this... allow the mage a snare-type spell, OR a speed-enhancing spell OR some kind of Fear. Any of these could be developed into a viable soloing strategy instead of the current "Stand and Fight" options we have.<P>There will be those who say that the "Soloability" of a mage should not be a measure of our effectiveness. For the most part I agree, but for many of us, that was part of the allure of he class. For a class with very little to offer a group otherwise, and nothing to offer that another Nuker couldn't offer, (often in a better way.. ala Mod Rod) it is VERY frustrating to be stuck with NO soloability and no group out there who wouldn't dump you for a chanter, or wiz who can at least evac...<P>My 2 cents...<P>--------------------<P>Thayn Bloodraven
</FONT>
